Coloration of holotype in preservative.
Background color of dorsum light brown-cream with a continuous large dark brown mark from snout to sacral region, only divided by a white, thin middorsal stripe and a white interorbital band (
Fig. 1
); upper lip with dark brown bars below eyes; dark brown supratympanic fold; silver and bronze brilliant sparkling distributed on dorsum; dark brown mark surrounding the cloaca; minute white dots on the flanks; dorsally, arms and legs with pink hue, barred thighs, forearm with one brown stripe; ventral coloration (including arms and legs) cream with numerous minute brown dots and scarce white dots seen under magnification (
Fig. 1
).

